ZCZC EE18
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 022300 UTC
A LARGE AND COMPLEX SLOW MOV LOW 995 OVER THE SERN NORWEGIAN SEA EXTENDS
A TROUGH S OVER THE BRITISH ISLES DURING TUESDAY. THIS TROUGH CLEARS E EARLY
WEDNESDAY WHILE THE LOW GRADUALLY FILLS AND MOVS S DURING WEDNESDAY. THIS
BROAD SLOW MOV LOW LIES W OF BAILEY AND ROCKALL WHILE A SECONDARY LOW DEVELOPS
IN THE ENGLISH CHANNEL LATE WEDNESDAY. THIS SECONDARY LOW TRACKS NE AND FILLS
OVER THE SERN N SEA EARLY THURSDAY AS HIGH PRESSURE OVER BISCAY STRETCHES
A RIDGE NE. MEANWHILE THE LOW W OF ROCKALL AND SHANNON TRACKS N LATE THURSDAY
INTO FRIDAY WHILE EXTENDING TROUGHS ACROSS WERN AREAS. GALES ARE NOT EXP
DURING THE FCST PERIOD. STRG WINDS ARE LIKELY FOR SHANNON AND SOLE ON THURSDAY
AND FRIDAY. STRG WINDS MAY AFFECT FITZROY PLYMOUTH AND FASTNET ON FRIDAY.
NO WIDESPREAD FOG IS EXP ACROSS THE AREA THROUGH THE PERIOD
